    • Constructor Detail

      • PrintForeachAction

        public PrintForeachAction(java.io.PrintWriter printWriter,
                  java.lang.String streamName)
        Print data message with given writer. The PrintWriter can be null in order to distinguish between System.out and the others. If the PrintWriter is PrintWriter(System.out), then it would close System.out output stream.

        Afterall, not to pass in PrintWriter(System.out) but null instead.

        Parameters:
        printWriter - Use System.out.println if null.
        streamName - The given name will be printed.
